<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="pleased-adj">pleased <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /pliːzd/    美 /pliːzd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>[不用于名词前]高兴的；满意的：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>(be) pleased to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her parents were so pleased to get the news that she won the prize. 
得知她获奖的消息，她的父母非常高兴。</p><footer>人教③ – 5</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) pleased + (that) 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Everyone is pleased that you’ve decided to come to the party. 
你决定来参加聚会大家都十分高兴。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) pleased with:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I am very pleased with the quality of your work. 
我对你的工作质量很满意。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-pleased-with-oneself">(be) pleased with oneself</h3>
<p>1.<strong>自鸣得意</strong>  </p></div>